data.title: "Soul Train" Sister Sledge/Ray Parker Jr. (TV Episode 1982)
data.meta_description: Sister Sledge/Ray Parker Jr.: Directed by J.D. Lobue. With Don Cornelius, Joe Cobb, Sid McCoy, Ray Parker Jr.. 1st song = "Work That Sucker To Death" by "Xavier" [ #6 R&B ]. 2nd song = "You're The One For Me" by "D-Train" [ #13 R&B ]. 1st lip-sync = "The Other Woman" by "Ray Parker Jr." [ #2 R&B ]. 3rd song = "Let's Work" by "Prince" [ #9 R&B ]. Flashback clip = "Baby Come Close" by "Smokey Robinson" [ #7 R&B/Pop ]. 4th song = "The Gigolo" by "O'Bryan" [ #5 R&B ]. 2nd lip-sync = "My Guy" by "Sister Sledge" [ #14 R&B ]. 5th song = "Genius Of Love" by "Tom Tom Club" [ #2 R&B ]. 3rd lip-sync = "Streetlove" by "Ray Parker Jr." [ LP Cut ]. Line Dance = "Let It Whip" by "Dazz Band" [ #1 R&B ]. 4th lip-sync = "All The Man That I Need" by "Kathy Sledge & David Simmons" [ #45 R&B ].
